import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['home_score'], bins=range(0, 12), edgecolor='black', color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.xlabel('Home Scores')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['home_score'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['away_score'].plot.hist(bins=10, alpha=0.5, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['away_score'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['away_score'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Away Scores')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of away scores?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['score_difference'] = data['home_score'] - data['away_score']
    plt.hist(data['score_difference'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Score Difference')
    plt.axvline(data['score_difference'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['score_difference'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Score Difference (Home - Away)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the difference between home and away scores?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    league_counts = data['division'].value_counts()
    league_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'green', 'red', 'orange', 'purple'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of matches played in each league?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('League')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Matches')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(league_counts.index, title='Leagues', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['year_month'] = data['date'].dt.to_period('M')
    matches_per_month = data.groupby('year_month').size()

    plt.plot(matches_per_month.index.to_timestamp(), matches_per_month.values)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of matches played over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Time')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Matches')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Matches per Month'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
